> Private Cloud Servers
	- ownCloud:
		-- Frank Karlitschek
		-- GNU AGPLv3
	
	- Nextcloud:
		-- forked from ownCloud
		-- Frank Karlitschek
		-- GNU AGPLv3

> Database Servers
	- MariaDB
		-- forked from MySQL
	- Firebird
	- PostgreSQL
	- SQL (Structure Query Language) 

> Email Servers
	- MTA (Mail Transfer Agent)
		-- Sendmail
		-- Postfix
	- MDA (Mail Delivery Agent)
	- POP/IMAP Server
		-- Devecot
		-- Cyrus IMAP
	- Microsoft Exchange

> File Sharing
	- Samba (Windows-centric)
	- Netatalk (Apple Macintosh-centric)
	- NFS (Network File Sharing): File sharing protocol for UNIX/Linux
	
	- Internet Software Consortium
		-- Maintains "Bind", the most popular DNS server.
		-- Maintains "ISC DHCP".
	
	- LDAP (Lightweight Directory Access Protocol)
		-- OpenLDAP

> Email 
	- Thunderbird (Desktop email client)
	- Evolution (Desktop email client)
	- Kmail (Desktop email client)

> Productivity
	- OpenOffic (also called OpenOffice.org) -> LibreOffce
============================================================================================================================================================

> Shell
	- Bourne shell
		-- Bash (Bourne Again Shell)
	- C shell
		-- tcsh
	- ksh (Korn shell)
	- zsh (Z shell)

> Text Editors
	- Vi (modern one Vim) & Emacs
	- Pico & Nano

> Package Management 
	- Debian Package Management
		-- .deb extension
		-- dpkg (lowest level)
		-- apt-get (Advance Package Tool, front-end to the dpkg tool)
		-- aptitude (a front-end to the dpkg tool)
		-- Synaptic (GUI front-end to the dpkg tool)
		-- Software Center (GUI front-end to the dpkg tool)

	- RPM Package Management
		-- Standard package management system, according to "Linux Standard Base".
		-- .rpm extension
		-- rpm (back-end tool)
		-- yum (front-end tool)
		-- up2date (front-end tool)
		-- Yumex (GUI tool)
		-- Gnome PackageKit (GUI tool)

		-- ZYpp (or libzypp)
			--- zypper

> Security
	- Gufw (GUI to "Ubuntu'S Uncomplicated Firewall (UFW))
	- iptables (built-in firewall system)

> Cloud 
	- VMware & Openbox
